{"name": "fairpredictor", "metadata": {"name": "fairpredictor", "version": "0.0.36", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/kshitijrajsharma/fairpredictor", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["requests", "Pillow", "rtree", "tqdm", "geopandas", "shapely", "rasterio", "orthogonalizer"], "summary": "A package for running predictions using fAIr", "upload_time": 1732553856}, "documentation": ["## fAIr Predictor\n \nRun your fAIr Model Predictions anywhere ! \n\n## Prerequisites\n\nfAIr Predictor has support for GPU , CPU and tflite based devices \n\n- Install ```tensorflow-cpu``` or ```tflite-runtime``` according to your requirements \n\n```tflite-runtime``` support is for having very light deployment in order to run inference & \n```tensorflow-cpu``` might require installation of ```efficientnet```\n\n## Example on Collab \n```python\n# Install \n!pip install fairpredictor\n\n# Import \nfrom predictor import predict\n\n# Parameters for your predictions \nbbox=[100.56228021333352,13.685230854641182,100.56383321235313,13.685961853747969]\nmodel_path='checkpoint.h5'\nzoom_level=20\ntms_url='https://tiles.openaerialmap.org/6501a65c0906de000167e64d/0/6501a65c0906de000167e64e/{z}/{x}/{y}'\n\n# Run your prediction \nmy_predictions=predict(bbox,model_path,zoom_level,tms_url)\nprint(my_predictions)\n\n## Visualize your predictions \n\nimport geopandas as gpd\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\ngdf = gpd.GeoDataFrame.from_features(my_predictions)\ngdf.plot()\nplt.show()\n```\n\nWorks on CPU ! Can work on serverless functions, No other dependencies to run predictions \n\n## Use raster2polygon \n\nThere is another postprocessing option that supports distance threshold between polygon for merging them , If it is useful for you install raster2polygon by : \n```\npip install raster2polygon\n```\n\n## Load Testing\n\n**CAUTION : Always take permission of server admin before you perform load test** \n\nIn order to perform load testing we use Locust , To enable this hit following command within the root dir \n\n- Install locust\n\n    ```\n    pip install locust\n    ```\n\n- Run locust script\n    ```\n    locust -f locust.py\n    ```\nPopulate your HOST and replace it with BASE URL of the Predictor URL \n\n\n## Docker \n\n### Build \n```bash\nsudo docker build . -t fairpredictor \n```\n\n### Run \n```bash\nsudo docker run --rm --name fairpredictor -v $(pwd):/mnt -p 8000:8000 fairpredictor\n```\n\n### Navigate to localhost:8000 and shoot following request body \n```json\n{\n  \"bbox\": [100.56228021333352, 13.685230854641182, 100.56383321235313, 13.685961853747969],\n  \"checkpoint\": \"/mnt/tests/checkpoints/ramp/checkpoint.tflite\",\n  \"zoom_level\": 20,\n  \"source\": \"https://tiles.openaerialmap.org/6501a65c0906de000167e64d/0/6501a65c0906de000167e64e/{z}/{x}/{y}\"\n}\n```\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "predictor.app", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "predictor.app.predict", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "bbox", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "model_path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "zoom_level", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tms_url", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tile_size", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "base_path", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "confidence", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "area_threshold", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "tolerance", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "tile_overlap_distance", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "use_raster2polygon", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "remove_metadata", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "orthogonalize", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "max_angle_change", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "skew_tolerance", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Parameters:\n    bbox : Bounding box of the area you want to run prediction on\n    model_path : Path of your downloaded model checkpoint\n    zoom_level : Zoom level of the tiles to be used for prediction\n    tms_url : Your Image URL on which you want to detect feature\n    tile_size : Optional >> Tile size to be used in pixel default : 256*256\n    base_path : Optional >> Basepath for your working dir of prediction\n    confidence: Optional >> Threshold probability for filtering out low-confidence predictions, Defaults to 0.5\n    area_threshold (float, optional): Threshold for filtering polygon areas. Defaults to 3 sqm.\n    tolerance (float, optional): Tolerance parameter for simplifying polygons. Defaults to 0.5 m. Percentage Tolerance = (Tolerance in Meters / Arc Length in Meters \u200b)\u00d7100\n    tile_overlap_distance : Provides tile overlap distance to remove the strip between predictions, Defaults to 0.15m"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "predictor.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "predictor.utils.get_start_end_download_coords", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "bbox_coords", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "zm_level", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tile_size", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "predictor.utils.download_image", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "url", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "base_path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "source_name", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "predictor.utils.convert2worldcd", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "lat", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lng", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tile_size", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["World coordinates  are measured from the Mercator projection's origin\n(the northwest corner of the map at 180 degrees longitude and\napproximately 85 degrees latitude) and increase in the x direction\ntowards the east (right) and increase in the y direction towards the south\n(down).Because the basic Mercator  tile is 256 x 256 pixels, the usable\nworld coordinate space is {0-256}, {0-256}"]}, {"name": "predictor.utils.latlng2tile", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "zoom", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lat", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lng", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tile_size", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["By dividing the pixel coordinates by the tile size and taking the\ninteger parts of the result, you produce as a by-product the tile\ncoordinate at the current zoom level."]}, {"name": "predictor.utils.tile_xy_to_quad_key", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "tile_x", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tile_y", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "level_of_detail", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "predictor.utils.download_imagery", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "start", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "end", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "zm_level", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "base_path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "source", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Downloads imagery from start to end tile coordinate system\n\nArgs:\n    start (list):[tile_x,tile_y]\n    end (list): [tile_x,tile_y],\n    source (string): it should be eithre url string or maxar value\n    zm_level : Zoom level"]}, {"name": "predictor.utils.get_bounding_box", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filename", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Get the EPSG:3857 coordinates of bounding box for the OAM image.\n\nThis function gives the coordinates of lower left and upper right\ncorners of the OAM image. We will use the bounding box to georeference\nthe image and for clipping and rasterizing the corresponding labels.\n\nReturns:\n    A tuple, (x_min, y_min, x_max, y_max), with coordinates in meters."]}, {"name": "predictor.utils.num2deg", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "x_tile", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "y_tile", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "zoom", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Convert tile numbers to EPSG:4326 coordinates.\n\nConvert tile numbers to the WGS84 longitude/latitude coordinates\n(in degrees) of the upper left corner of the tile.\n\nArgs:\n    x_tile: Tile X coordinate\n    y_tile: Tile Y coordinate\n    zoom: Level of detail\n\nReturns:\n    A tuple (longitude, latitude) in degrees."]}, {"name": "predictor.utils.open_images_keras", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "paths", "type": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "np.ndarray", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.ndarray", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Open images from some given paths."]}, {"name": "predictor.utils.open_images_pillow", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "paths", "type": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "np.ndarray", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.ndarray", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Open images from given paths using Pillow and resize them."]}, {"name": "predictor.utils.remove_files", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pattern", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Remove files matching a wildcard."]}, {"name": "predictor.utils.save_mask", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "mask", "type": {"name": "np.ndarray", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.ndarray", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "filename", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": nu